Description: Developer of mobile and integrated payment applications for QuickBooks and QuickBooks POS users.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Pensmore Software was founded in October 2011. During the years leading up to launch, our founder ran a CRM company that provided SaaS and On Premise solutions to the QuickBooks user base. As the business grew, they looked for tools to help them scale while also reducing costs. A key area in which they could do this was merchant processing. Within the market, there was only one integrated solution with QuickBooks & QuickBooks Point of Sales, Intuit's own Merchant Services. So we decided to invest our own time, energy and money into creating an integration truly designed with the QuickBooks user and merchant in mind. We then decided to partner with Mercury Payment Systems as they provided far superior service and focused on a "dealer centric" model that ensured the customer was well supported. With the formal rollout in January of this year, we have seen the solution immediately embraced by other small businesses and dealers alike. Looking for a simpler and better way to work, these business found that Pensmore was a system that worked for them, not the other way around. Today, Pensmore continues to grow exponentially and continues to bring the best QuickBooks focused merchant integrations to market. Pensmore Software is headquartered in Charlotte, NC and has locations in Denver and Durango, CO. Each day we come together to listen to our customers & dealers, solve problems and continue to improve our products.

Full Description: ex24 WAS PREVIOUSLY REGISTERED WITH THE U.S. SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION(SEC). ex24 PROPOSES TO USE THIS FUNDING TO RE-REGISTER WITH THE SEC ex24, with its  technology platform written in Java , managed by  its majority shareholder as CEO,   previously operated as a Person to Person, 24/7,   broker-less, major stock trading and settlement system.  ex24 was  an SEC registered Alternative Trading System(ATS), operating as a  Self Clearing  Broker/ Dealer.  Because of a rule,  limiting trades to 99 shares per order, from which ex24 unsuccessfully sought exemption,  the system was shuttered as unprofitable in 2006 after a cash investment of more than $9 million by its Founder, James P. Lennane.  ex24 traded solely in large cap Listed Securities. It closed its operation with a flawless record. Mr. Lennane now proposes to become the U.S. premier, SEC registered, Title III Crowdfunding issue support system, a Title III Crowdfunding  trading platform, a transaction settlement  system, and a stock holder record management system. Initially,  ex24 will conduct Funding Portal activities. However, after proving its core system, ex24'a long range goal is provide a full service initiation and initial funding services  to SEC Registered Broker/Dealers Funding Portals and Title III Crowdfunding Issuers thus relieving them  of the detailed burdens of an SEC Regulatory compliance for Crowdfunding by an Issuer. Further ex24 will perform the stock records maintenance and transfer services to Issuers once the Issuer's Crowdfunding is completed. Subsequent to Title III Issues having passed through the mandatory one year holding period, ex24 will provide a complete trading platform for buying, selling and selling the previously issued Title III securities in a safe and secure already proven environment.. ex24 will use the proceeds of the offering to apply to  be registered with the SEC as a Self Clear Broker/ Dealer that  will be permitted to carry Customer funds and Securities.

Description: OblakSoft is focused on developing technology solutions to optimize cloud storage.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: OblakSoft focuses on technologies that simplify adoption of cloud computing.  OblaskSoft offers ClouSE – a technology that allows cloud storage to be "plugged into" MySQL in a seamless and secure manner. ClouSE is the Cloud Storage Engine for MySQL that can utilize cloud storage such as Amazon S3 to store relational and blob data.  ClouSE provides fully functional, transactional and ACID-compliant relational data management on top of cloud storage. Key advantages of ClouSE include: * It provides transactional (ACID) guarantees to the users, with transactions featuring commit, rollback, and crash-recovery capabilities to protect user data * It allows utilizing cloud storage to store user data * It supports on-the-fly encryption of user data to guarantee its full confidentiality in the cloud * It supports direct access to blob content (a.k.a. weblobs) to enable scaling out content delivery of large data objects (e.g. pictures, movies) * It supports public, private and hybrid cloud configurations Designed and optimized for cloud storage from ground up ClouSE uses eventual consistency management, compression and caching techniques to smooth out cloud storage adoption bumps such as non-strict data consistency, high-latency storage access, and higher storage access failure rate due to network failures.  As a transactional storage engine for MySQL ClouSE opens cloud storage to SQL developers and SQL-based applications and reduces the need to retrain developers and rewrite applications to use new data processing paradigms, thus lowering the barrier for cloud storage adoption.

Full Description: What is Ryngly?  Ryngly is conference calling redefined. A new take on meetings and group conversations built on simplicity. At the core, Ryngly addresses the challenges with conference calls by quickly connecting you with others. No more having to dial-in to your call, we simply call you when it is time to meet. Join a work meeting, chat with friends, or check in on your family. Ryngly makes it as simple as answering the phone to start the conversation, and is the perfect solution for anyone, anytime, anywhere.    Why Ryngly?        -Did you know that on average, 15 minutes of every conference call is wasted on late joiners and participants having trouble connecting to the call? With the ability to schedule or create on demand calls, you can be sure     your calls start on time, every time. That’s 15 minutes of your day you can have back!      -Ryngly offers other options for reaching your contacts. Ryngly can send text, voice (think voice message), and email alerts all from one place.       -No subscriptions, commitments, or hidden fees. Only pay for what you use.      -Go Mobile! Access all Ryngly features at the palm of your hand. Easily manage and join your conference or group calls from anywhere, anytime. Available for download on iOS and Android.    What else can Ryngly do?      -Need to connect with others immediately? Use Ryngly’s Quickfire option to contact a group quickly and easily. Launch a call or notification at a moment's notice.      -Manage the call with a secure dashboard. See who joined, add others, re-dial, mute, or even remove the participants      -Schedule your meetings and let Ryngly do the rest. Create groups to easily manage your teams.    How much does Ryngly cost?      -Pay-as-you-go means that you only pay for what you use. No monthly subscriptions or hidden fees.       -Calls and voice alerts are $.02 cents/minute/user. Text and emails are $.02/message.    How do I sign-up?      -Go to ryngly.com and click sign-up. Create a free Ryngly account and start exploring the easy-to-use application.      -Want to start your first call or send an alert? Under your Account settings, simply input your credit card information and choose how much you’d like to spend.  The balance is yours to use whenever you would like. It’s that simple!

Mahi's flagship product, the Mahi Mi7, is a 320 Gbit multi-service switching system. It also offers a Vx7 Multi-Service Core Transport System with ROADM capabilities. To support the increasing demand for IP and SAN services, Mahi Networks introduced a 10-port Multi-Service ADM Transponder with SFP client interfaces supporting any combination of GbE, Fiber Channel, ESCON, FICON, and digital video services. In addition, Mahi offers a 10G Multi-Service Transponder with XFP client interfaces supporting 10GbE LAN PHY, 10GbE WAN PHY, OC-192, STM-64, and G.709 services. Mahi Networks was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Piscataway, New Jersey. Later on, Mahi Networks, Inc. was acquired by Meriton Networks, Inc.

Description: SupportContracts.com develops an innovative solution for the IT industry with its SPRT Marketplace and SPRT Manager platform.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: SupportContracts.com introduces a unique solution to the IT industry through its SPRT Marketplace and SPRT Manager platform. This platform aims to address the challenges IT administrators face in managing their assets, warranties, software licenses, MSP agreements, and support contracts. The SPRT Marketplace serves as the industry's first renewals marketplace, offering a central platform where IT administrators can explore and compare various support contracts and service renewals from different vendors. Meanwhile, the SPRT Manager is a cloud-based, multi-vendor support management platform. It allows IT administrators to proactively oversee their assets, warranties, software licenses, and MSP agreements. The platform also provides tools to generate reports, aiding administrators in gaining insights into contract statuses, asset inventories, and other relevant metrics. Additionally, the platform streamlines the renewal process, making it more efficient and reducing manual tasks. By combining these features, SupportContracts.com's offerings enable IT administrators to more effectively manage their IT assets and contracts, contributing to improved operational efficiency and informed decision-making within the IT domain.
